I need to convert a set of MIDI files to JAMS files, but I only want to extract the notes of one "track" (or instrument) from each MIDI file, and I know the name of that track. I've been playing around with `pretty_midi` but haven't been able to get at this information. As an example, if I import one of these MIDI files into GarageBand I can see the track names: http://i.imgur.com/ziGf3I7.png

Is there a way to extract this information using `pretty_midi`?

In the context of lexical ambiguity it would be nice to have a way to define which lexeme is preferred over which.

For example:
```
terminals:
a: {>b, >c};
b: ;
c: ;
```
In case of ambiguity between `a` and either `b` or `c`, `a` will be preferred.

Ordering graph should be pre-calculated and cycles reported. Disambiguation will be done dynamically.

Hi

I have  a table with two columns like name and address for example.
For the name field, the search should be a strict-search (exact match), but the address field should not be strict (so I can type in the first letters of the street).

I know the custom filter method to make the whole table search strict:

<table st-set-filter="myFilter" st-table="myData">

`angular.module('myApp').filter('myFilter',
  function($filter) {
    return function(input, predicate) {
      return $filter('filter')(input, predicate, true);
    };
  }
);`

But I can't find a solution to achieve strict search for a single column, for example only for the name.
How can I do this?

Thanks a lot,
Miro

